iptables is a front-end to the Netfilter firewall, implemented in the Linux kernel.

iptables -> Tables -> Chains -> Rules

iptables has the following built-in tables:

- Filter table - default one; if a table isn't specified, the filter table will be used
	iptables --list (without the -t argument) - displays the Filter table rules

	INPUT
	OUTPUT
	FORWARD

- NAT Table
- Mangle Table
- Raw Table

Select a table

	iptables -t filter --list

iptables -F

	flush iptables rules

iptables-save

